-- BofA Hires Wood to Head U.S. Energy Investment Banking Group
-- B y   S a n a t   V a l l i k a p p e n
-- 2012-05-17T03:34:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-17/bofa-hires-wood-to-head-u-s-energy-investment-banking-group.html
Bank of America Corp.  hired Ray Wood
from Credit Suisse Group AG to head its U.S. power and energy
investment banking group, according to a company memo.  Wood will report to Laurie Coben and Julian Mylchreest,
global co-heads for energy and power, the two said in an
internal memo obtained by Bloomberg News. Wood held the same
position at Credit Suisse.  Gavin Wolfe and Jason Satsky, also from Credit Suisse, will
join the  Charlotte , North Carolina-based bank as managing
directors reporting to Wood. All three will be based in  New
York , the memo said.  John Yiannacopoulos, a spokesman at Bank of America,
confirmed the contents of the memo. The Wall Street Journal
reported the hirings earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
